  "body": "I was a bit hacking the render function with this function: https://jsfiddle.net/crl/arshc5nk/11/\n\n```\nfunction renderReplace(component, container){\n  var temp = document.createElement(\"div\");\n  ReactDOM.render(component, temp);\n  container.parentNode.replaceChild(temp.firstElementChild, container);\n}\n```\n\n(I need to replace the node where react injects the component, for making sure it won't break a UI layout\n\n```\n  <div class=\"row\">\n    <div data-region=\"main\"></div>\n    <div data-region=\"sidebar\"></div>\n  </div>\n```\n\nthe components injected contain a `class=\"column\"`, so if I keep the extra wrapping div's with data-region it can breaks the UI)\n\nSo I used the function above, but what's weird is the inline event handler don't work anymore, it works with addEventHandler though, but the style are preserved, that seems inconsistent\n",
